text: Haaren is a village and former municipality in the Dutch province of North Brabant. In 2019, 14,195 people lived there. Since 2021, it is part of four municipalities: Boxtel, Oisterwijk, Tilburg, and Vught. The village of Haaren itself is part of the municipality of Oisterwijk.
